.\" Man page for ataegina.
.\" Kept in sync by hand with the `usage()` text in the ataegina script.
.TH ATAEGINA 1 "2026-07-19" "ataegina" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ataegina \- worktree-aware dev launcher: collision-free ports, processes, and databases
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ataegina
.I init
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B ataegina
.I up
.RB [ both | backend | frontend ]
.RB [ --scope
.IR X ]
.br
.B ataegina
.I down
.RB [ both | backend | frontend ]
.RB [ --force ]
.br
.B ataegina
.I restart
.RB [ both | backend | frontend ]
.RB [ --scope
.IR X ]
.br
.B ataegina
.I logs
.RB [ both | backend | frontend ]
.RB [ -n
.IR N ]
.RB [ --no-follow ]
.br
.B ataegina
.I db
.RB [ name | url | create | drop ]
.br
.B ataegina
.I open
.RB [ frontend | backend ]
.br
.B ataegina
.RB { ports | env | list | move
.IR N | prune | doctor }
.br
.B ataegina
.I exec
.RB [ \-\- ]
.I CMD
.RI [ args .\|.\|.]
.br
.B ataegina
.I config
.RB [ list | get | set | unset | path ]
.br
.B ataegina
.I completion
.RB { bash | zsh }
.br
.B ataegina
.RB { update | --version | --help }
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ataegina
gives every git worktree \(em and every AI coding agent working in one \(em its
own collision-free runtime: derived ports, tracked processes, and an isolated
per-worktree database, from a single zero-dependency bash script. No Docker, no
daemon, no YAML.
.PP
The moment you run more than one copy of a repo at once, the stack collides:
dev servers fight for the same ports, share one dev database, and leak untracked
background processes. ataegina assigns each worktree an index (the primary
checkout is always index 0) and derives its ports as
.IR FRONT_PORT_BASE + N " and " BACK_PORT_BASE + N ,
so N worktrees coexist on the bare host.
.PP
Run
.B ataegina init
once to detect your stack and write a declarative
.IR ataegina.config.sh .
Its built-in hooks read that config, so most users never write any bash.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init \fR[options]
Detect the frontend and backend and write
.IR ataegina.config.sh .
Interactive by default; each detected value is offered as the prompt default.
.TP
.B up \fR[both|backend|frontend] [--scope X]
Start dev servers for this worktree (default: both). Ensures the per-worktree
database exists first (when configured). Reports each server as ready, still
starting, or failed. If the slot port is held by a process ataegina did not
start, it says so and does not launch on top of it.
.TP
.B down \fR[both|backend|frontend] [--force]
Stop this worktree's servers, reaping the whole process tree (workers and
helpers, not just the port holder). A slot held by a process ataegina did not
start is left alone;
.B --force
(or
.BR ATE_DOWN_FORCE=1 )
reaps it anyway.
.TP
.B restart \fR[both|backend|frontend] [--scope X]
Stop this worktree's servers, then start them again \(em a
.B down
followed by an
.BR up .
All arguments are forwarded to
.BR up ,
which resolves the final scope; the stop phase mirrors the mode word, so
.B restart backend
bounces only the backend and leaves a running frontend alone.
.TP
.B logs \fR[both|backend|frontend] [-n N] [--no-follow]
Follow this worktree's server logs.
.TP
.B db \fR[name|url|create|drop]
Inspect or manage this worktree's database. With no argument, prints the derived
database name.
.TP
.B ports
Show this worktree's index, derived ports, and URLs.
.TP
.B open \fR[frontend|backend]
Open this worktree's derived URL in a browser (default
.BR frontend ).
The opener is
.B $BROWSER
if set (it may carry its own flags), else
.B xdg-open
on Linux, else
.B open
on macOS; if none is available the URL is printed so you can open it yourself.
.TP
.B env " [\-\-no\-export]"
Print this worktree's derived environment (index, ports, URLs, log dir, and the
per\-worktree database name and URL when configured) as eval\-able shell \(em the
same variables
.B up
injects into your dev servers. Use
.B eval \(dq$(ataegina env)\(dq
to load it into your own shell;
.B \-\-no\-export
omits the
.B export
prefix so the output can be redirected to a
.I .env
file. Read\-only.
.TP
.BR exec " [\-\-] " \fICMD " [" \fIargs .\|.\|.]
Run
.I CMD
with this worktree's derived environment injected (the same variables
.B env
prints), inheriting stdio and the current directory, and exit with
.IR CMD 's
status. The one\-shot form of
.BR "eval \(dq$(ataegina env)\(dq" ,
e.g.
.BR "ataegina exec \-\- pytest" .
An optional
.B \-\-
separates ataegina's arguments from the command.
.TP
.B list
Show all registered worktrees and their indices.
.TP
.B move \fIN
Relocate this worktree to index
.IR N ,
assigning a new port pair. Useful when the auto-assigned slot's ports are
permanently taken. The primary (index 0) cannot be moved.
.TP
.B prune
Drop registry entries whose worktree directory no longer exists, freeing those
indices for reuse.
.TP
.B doctor
Read-only diagnostics for this worktree: resolved index, ports, port-probe tool,
config source, start hooks, and database status.
.TP
.B config \fR[list|get|set|unset|path]
Read or write scalar keys in
.IR ataegina.config.sh .
With no subcommand, lists every known key, its effective value, and its source.
.TP
.B update
Self-update the installed script to the latest published release (checksum
verified, with a backup of the previous version).
.TP
.B completion \fR{bash|zsh}
Print a shell completion script to stdout, completing subcommands and one level
of common arguments. Load it with
.B "source <(ataegina completion bash)"
(or
.BR zsh ).
Needs no worktree. Both
.B ataegina
and the
.B ate
alias are completed.
.TP
.B --version ", " -v
Print the version and exit.
.TP
.B --help ", " -h
Print usage and exit.
.SH "UP OPTIONS"
.TP
.B --scope X
Force the start scope:
.IR frontend | backend | both | none .
Without it, the scope is auto-detected from the worktree's git diff (or read from
a
.RI ` scope: '
line in
.BR $ATE_TASK_FILE ,
if set). Index 0 (the primary) is always both.
.SH "INIT OPTIONS"
.TP
.B --yes ", " -y ", " --non-interactive
Accept all detected values with no prompts (as in CI).
.TP
.B --frontend-dir \fIDIR\fR ", " --backend-dir \fIDIR
Force the frontend/backend directory, skipping probing.
.TP
.B --force
Overwrite an existing
.IR ataegina.config.sh .
.TP
.B --dry-run
Print the generated config to stdout and write nothing.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ATE_INDEX=\fIn
Force a specific index for one invocation.
.TP
.B ATE_CONFIG=\fIpath
Use an explicit config file path.
.TP
.B ATE_REGISTRY_DIR ", " ATE_REGISTRY
Override the registry location.
.TP
.B ATE_SCOPE_AUTO=0
Disable scope auto-detection in
.B up
(force both).
.TP
.B ATE_BASE_BRANCH
Base ref that scope detection diffs against.
.TP
.B ATE_DOWN_FORCE=1
Make
.B down
reap a slot held by a process ataegina did not start (same as
.BR "down --force" ).
.TP
.B ATE_PORT_TOOL
Force the port-probe backend:
.IR lsof | ss | fuser | proc | none
(auto-detected otherwise).
.TP
.B ATE_UPDATE_CHECK=1
Opt in to a throttled (at most once per 24h) "newer version" notice at the end of
.BR up .
Off by default. One GET to the public GitHub API; silent on failure. No other
telemetry.
.TP
.B GH_TOKEN
Optional GitHub token, sent as a bearer to the release feed.
.SH "CONFIG KEYS"
Set in
.IR ataegina.config.sh ;
see
.IR ataegina.config.example.sh .
.TP
.B FRONT_PORT_BASE ", " BACK_PORT_BASE
Port bases (default 5173 / 8000).
.TP
.B FRONTEND_DIR ", " FRONTEND_CMD ", " FRONTEND_ENV
Declarative frontend directory, start command, and extra env.
.TP
.B BACKEND_DIR ", " BACKEND_CMD ", " BACKEND_ENV
Declarative backend directory, start command, and extra env.
.TP
.B DB_NAME
Set to enable per-worktree databases (off when unset).
.TP
.B DB_KIND
.IR postgres | mysql | sqlite | custom
(default postgres).
.TP
.B DB_SUFFIX
Worktree DB name =
.IR DB_NAME + DB_SUFFIX + N
(default _wt).
.TP
.B DB_URL_TEMPLATE ", " DB_URL_VAR
Build and inject the per-worktree connection URL.
.TP
.B DB_AUTO_CREATE
.B up
ensures the worktree DB exists (default 1).
.TP
.B DB_CREATE_CMD ", " DB_DROP_CMD
Override the per-kind create/drop commands.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ataegina.config.sh
Per-repo declarative configuration, at the repository root.
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/ataegina/ataegina.config.sh
Global configuration (written by
.BR "config set --global" ).
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success. A usage error exits 2; other failures exit nonzero with a
message on standard error.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Configure a repo and bring up its stack:
.EX
ataegina init --yes
ataegina up
.EE
.TP
Start only the backend for the current worktree:
.EX
ataegina up backend
.EE
.TP
Clear a slot even if held by an unrelated process:
.EX
ataegina down --force
.EE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR git-worktree (1).
Project homepage: https://github.com/noahhyden/ataegina-cli
